-- 
U.K. Urged to Disclose Women Seeking Board Seats, Observer Says

-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 
2011-02-20T09:11:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/u-k-urged-to-disclose-women-seeking-board-seats-observer-says.html
Leading British companies may be
obliged to disclose how many women they shortlist for each
boardroom vacancy under plans being considered by U.K.
government advisers,  The Observer  reported.    Mervyn Davies , a former U.K. trade minister who will
deliver his report to ministers this week, told the newspaper in
an interview that shareholders should put more pressure on
boards and on chairmen to recruit more women.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  